As to what you say about our house2—or rather its site — I for my part shall consider my restoration to be complete only when I find that it has been re- stored to me. But these things are not in our hands: what troubles me is, that in the outlay which must be incurred you, unhappy and impoverished as you are, must necessarily share. However‚ if we succeed in our object, I shall recover everything3 but then, if ill- fortune continues to persecute us, are you, my poor dear‚ to be allowed to throw away what you may have saved from the wreck‘?
